cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a neural sequence-to-sequence model for direction following, which involves natural language processing and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses long short-term memory recurrent neural networks (LSTM-RNN), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves mapping instructions to action sequences, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or robotics (cs.RO).
